window.EQ_DATA["META"] = {"ticker": "META", "meta": {"ticker": "META", "nome_empresa": "Meta Platforms, Inc.", "setor": "Internet / Digital Advertising", "geografia": "US", "moeda_reporte": "USD", "market_cap_usd_bn": "~1700", "shares_outstanding_bn": "~2.5", "fiscal_year_end": "31 de dezembro (FY25 = year ended 2025-12-31)", "tags": ["setor/internet", "setor/digital-ads", "setor/ai-infra", "geografia/us", "moat/rede", "moat/dados", "status/posicao"], "status_tese": "posicao", "data_criacao": "2026-04-20", "ultima_atualizacao": "2026-05-27", "docs_pendentes_ocr": 16}, "views": {"ov": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h1>META — Meta Platforms, Inc.</h1>\n<blockquote><strong>One-liner</strong>: #2 player global em digital ads (atrás do Google), dono de Facebook/Instagram/WhatsApp/Threads/Ray-Ban Meta. Em transformação de &quot;social network&quot; pra &quot;AI infrastructure + content platform&quot; sob <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=mark-zuckerberg\" title=\"_people/mark-zuckerberg\">Zuckerberg</a>. Está no meio do maior ciclo de CapEx da sua história (<strong>$125-145B guide FY26</strong> — raised novamente em Q1 FY26 call de 29-Apr-2026).</blockquote></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>O negócio</h2><h3>O que a empresa faz</h3>\n<p>Meta opera duas unidades de negócio contábeis:</p>\n<ol><li><strong>Family of Apps (FoA)</strong> — 97% da receita. Inclui Facebook, Instagram, WhatsApp, Threads, Messenger. Quase toda receita vem de <strong>digital advertising</strong>. Click-to-Message ($10B+ ARR em FB/IG) e WhatsApp business messaging ($2B ARR) são avenidas novas.</li><li><strong>Reality Labs (RL)</strong> — ~1% da receita. AR/VR hardware (Quest headsets, Ray-Ban Meta glasses, Project Orion). Prejuízos operacionais <strong>cumulativos &gt;$79B</strong> (Q4/25), <strong>~$19B/ano em FY25</strong>. Pivotou de &quot;metaverse&quot; pra &quot;wearables&quot; — Ray-Ban Meta vendeu 7M+ unidades em FY25 (82% market share de smart glasses). Parceria com EssilorLuxottica expandida ($5.4B equity stake, 15,000+ retail locations).</li></ol>\n<p>Fundada em <strong>2004</strong> (como &quot;thefacebook&quot;) por Mark Zuckerberg em Harvard. HQ: Menlo Park, CA. IPO 2012.</p>\n<h3>Segmentos e geografia</h3>\n<p><strong>Receita FY25 por segmento</strong> (em $M):</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Segmento</th><th>FY25</th><th>FY24</th><th>YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Family of Apps</td><td>198,759</td><td>162,355</td><td>+22.4%</td></tr><tr><td>Reality Labs</td><td>2,207</td><td>2,146</td><td>+2.8%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td><strong>200,966</strong></td><td><strong>164,501</strong></td><td><strong>+22.2%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Geografia (FY25)</strong> — aproximado, a precisar no 10-K:</p>\n<ul><li>US &amp; Canada: ~50%</li><li>Europa: ~16% (~$32B)</li><li>Ásia-Pacífico: ~20% (fastest growing)</li><li>Resto do mundo: ~14%</li></ul>\n<p>ARPU US ≈ $230, ARPU China ≈ $20 (10-K FY2023). Upside se emerging markets convergem.</p>\n<h3>KPIs de usuário</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Family DAP</strong>: <strong>3.56B em Mar/2026</strong> (-0.6% QoQ — outage Iran + bloqueio WhatsApp Russia, Susan: &quot;absent these impacts, growth in family daily active people would have been positive QoQ&quot;). Vs 3.58B Q4/25 e 2.36B em Q1/20.</li><li><strong>Threads MAU</strong>: 320-400M (vs. 6.25% engagement vs X&#x27;s 3.6%) — Q1 FY26: continua trajetória de &quot;leading app in its category&quot;</li><li><strong>Threads DAU</strong>: <strong>150M+ em Q1 FY26 (follow-up call, Susan)</strong>; ads expanded to <strong>200+ países</strong>; growth in priority markets US + Japan; priority verticals = NBA, K-pop, reality TV (creator partnerships)</li><li><strong>WhatsApp Status ads</strong>: <strong>&quot;hundreds of millions of viewers per day&quot;</strong> Q1 FY26 (follow-up call) — popular em LatAm/Ásia/África, often outpaces Instagram in posting; ads click-to-website + reach/impressions/video views agora suportados; global rollout completo previsto pra 2026</li><li><strong>Meta AI MAU</strong>: 1B (zero receita standalone até agora) — Q1/26: &quot;double-digit % increases em sessions per user&quot; pós-rollout do Muse Spark; Meta AI app consistently near top of app stores</li><li><strong>Business AI weekly conversations</strong>: <strong>&gt;10M em Q1 FY26</strong> (vs <strong>1M no início do ano</strong> — <strong>10x growth</strong>)</li><li><strong>AI-translated videos weekly</strong>: <strong>&gt;500M users em CADA (FB e IG)</strong> (Q1 FY26)</li><li><strong>AI Glasses daily users</strong>: <strong>triplicou YoY</strong> (Q1 FY26 — Mark)</li><li><strong>Ray-Ban Meta units</strong>: 7M+ em FY25 (3x do acumulado 2023+2024)</li></ul>\n<h3>Drivers de receita atual</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Ad impressions</strong>: cresceram de +35% pra mid-single digits; <strong>growth agora é price-driven, não volume-driven</strong>. Q1 FY26: impressions <strong>+19% YoY</strong> (volta de impression growth via newer surfaces — Threads, WhatsApp, ads &amp; status)</li><li><strong>Price/ad</strong>: <strong>+12% YoY em Q1 FY26</strong> (vs +5% Q4 FY25, +9% FY25 inteiro) — <strong>aceleração</strong> via ad performance improvements + better macro + currency tailwind</li><li><strong>AI ad stack</strong>: GEM (engagement), Lattice, Andromeda, Sequence Learning, <strong>Adaptive Ranking (1T params)</strong> — ganhos compoundam multiplicativamente</li><li><strong>Advantage+</strong>: $60B+ ARR (de $20B em início de 2024 — 3x em 18m)</li><li><strong>Reels</strong>: $50B+ ARR (de $10B em mid-2023 — 5x)</li><li><strong>GenAI creative tools</strong>: $10B ARR — Q1 FY26 update: <strong>&gt;8M advertisers</strong> usando ≥1 ferramenta (vs <strong>4M end of 2024</strong> — 2x em ~16 meses, <strong>maioria SMBs</strong>, follow-up call); <strong>+3% conversion rate</strong> com video generation feature em large-scale test (transforma múltiplas imagens em vídeo multi-scene com text overlays + music); features expandindo: image animation (IG Reels, FB Reels, FB Feed, IG Stories), video filters (auto contrast/color), music generation (context-aware), voiceover translation, image overlay translation</li><li><strong>🆕 Meta AI Business Assistant</strong> (Q1 FY26 follow-up — Susan to Stephen Ju UBS): novo produto B2B que ajuda advertisers a <strong>otimizar campaigns</strong>, adjacente aos ad-creative tools. Susan framing: <em>&quot;in connection with the ad-creative tools ... should make it easier for businesses to manage, create, optimize their ad campaigns. And as we improve performance, that should accrue to revenue.&quot;</em> — primeiro vetor explícito de <strong>Meta AI monetizando o lado business</strong> (não consumer). Combina com Meta AI Shopping mode no lado consumer = ataque dos dois lados do funnel de commerce.</li><li><strong>Click-to-Message</strong>: $10B+ ARR em FB/IG, 60%+ YoY</li><li><strong>WhatsApp Business + paid messaging</strong>: Q1 FY26: FoA other revenue <strong>$885M, +74% YoY</strong></li><li><strong>Value Optimization Suite</strong>: <strong>&gt;$20B ARR em Q1 FY26 (doubled YoY)</strong> — helps advertisers maximize ROAS</li><li><strong>Creator partnerships ads</strong>: <strong>&gt;$10B ARR em Q1 FY26 (doubled YoY)</strong> — vetor novo</li><li><strong>Ray-Ban Meta</strong>: $2.2B revenue FY25 ($955M Q4 sozinho); Q1 FY26: AI Glasses tripling daily users YoY</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Stack técnico de monetização — deep dive</h2><p>Adicionado <strong>2026-04-27</strong> via <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-No-Priors-Matt-Steiner-Meta-Ad-System\" title=\"raw-md/META/2026-No-Priors-Matt-Steiner-Meta-Ad-System\">interview de Matt Steiner</a> (Meta VP of Monetization Infrastructure, Ranking &amp; AI Foundations) no <strong>No Priors Episode 68</strong> (Elad Gil + Sarah Guo). Steiner é o operador da máquina de monetização da Meta — direta autoridade sobre o stack.</p>\n<h3>Escala operacional do ad system</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>3+ bilhões de DAUs</strong> servidos com ads</li><li><strong>Sub-200ms latency</strong> por request</li><li><strong>&quot;Always-on&quot; infrastructure</strong> — zero downtime tolerável</li><li>Meta self-positioning: <strong>&quot;hardware and AI foundation company&quot;</strong>, não software-only</li></ul>\n<h3>Arquitetura em 4 camadas (do raw → ranked → served)</h3>\n<h4>1. Andromeda (retrieval / triagem)</h4>\n<ul><li><strong>Triagem de millions de ads candidatas</strong> para encontrar set retrievable em sub-second</li><li>Roda em <strong>custom NVIDIA Grace Hopper SKU co-designed por Meta</strong> — otimizado para <strong>memory-bound workloads</strong> (move o &quot;Personalization Blob&quot; do user através do sistema)</li><li><strong>First layer of hardware moat</strong>: Meta não é &quot;cliente comum&quot; da NVDA, é <strong>co-designer</strong> de SKU específico. Implicação: relação estratégica, não commodity buyer.</li></ul>\n<h4>2. Lattice (unified ranking model)</h4>\n<ul><li><strong>Modelo único</strong> consolidando o que antes eram modelos separados para Feed, Stories e Reels</li><li><strong>Transfer learning cross-property</strong>: clique em IG Reel ajuda predição em FB Feed</li><li>Compounding data advantage que TikTok/Snap/Pinterest não têm (não têm cross-property scale)</li></ul>\n<h4>3. GEM (Generative Ads Model)</h4>\n<ul><li><strong>Foundation model treinado em &quot;semantics&quot; de ads</strong></li><li>Entende <strong>conteúdo visual/contextual</strong> sem precisar de tags explícitas (ex: reconhece &quot;camping gear&quot; em uma imagem)</li><li><strong>Resposta direta ao Apple ATT (2021)</strong>: Meta agora <strong>não depende de signals explícitos</strong> de tracking — lê visual/contextual</li><li><strong>Implicação</strong>: privacy-first targeting. Defesa estrutural contra próximas rodadas de regulação privacy.</li></ul>\n<h4>4. Adaptive Ranking (real-time signal processing)</h4>\n<ul><li><strong>~1 trilhão de parâmetros</strong> servido em sub-second latency</li><li><strong>Real-time pivot</strong>: usuário gasta 5 segundos extra em conteúdo X → próximo swipe já reflete</li><li><strong>&quot;Real-time signal processing is what differentiates Meta from competitors&quot;</strong> — Steiner explícito</li></ul>\n<h3>Hardware moat — silicon co-design + KernelEvolve</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>MTIA</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MTIA\" title=\"_concepts/MTIA\">Meta Training and Inference Accelerator</a>): silicon proprietário em ramp para inference. <strong>Permite rodar modelos 1T params economicamente</strong> — impossível em standard infra.</li><li><strong>KernelEvolve</strong>: sistema interno onde <strong>LLMs escrevem software para os custom chips da Meta</strong>. Otimiza basic code instructions (kernels) em velocidade humanamente impossível.</li><li><strong>Loop recursivo</strong>: AI otimiza AI infrastructure. Cada geração de modelo melhora a próxima.</li></ul>\n<h3>KernelEvolve — deep dive técnico (Apr/2026 update)</h3>\n<p>Adicionado <strong>2026-04-27</strong> via <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-04-KernelEvolve-Engineering-at-Meta\" title=\"raw-md/META/2026-04-KernelEvolve-Engineering-at-Meta\">Engineering at Meta blog post (Apr/2 2026)</a> + <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-No-Priors-Matt-Steiner-Meta-Ad-System\" title=\"raw-md/META/2026-No-Priors-Matt-Steiner-Meta-Ad-System\">interview Steiner</a>. Companion paper at <strong>ISCA 2026</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>KernelEvolve</strong> é um <strong>sistema agêntico de geração de kernels</strong> — não é one-shot LLM code gen, é <strong>search-based</strong> (MCTS + evolutionary tree) avaliando centenas de candidatos com job-harness customizado.</p>\n<p><strong>Resultados em produção quantificados:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>+60% inference throughput</strong> em modelo Andromeda Ads em <strong>NVIDIA GPUs</strong></li><li><strong>+60% inference throughput</strong> em ads model em <strong>MTIA silicon</strong> (custom Meta)</li><li>KernelBench (Stanford 250 problems): kernels gerados são correct + faster que PyTorch reference em 480 hardware configurations</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Arquitetura de 6 componentes:</strong></p>\n<ol><li><strong>LLM Synthesizer</strong> — multiplos backends: Claude Code + OpenAI + Meta LLM. Dynamic, context-aware prompts continuamente refinados via signals de prior evaluation</li><li><strong>Tree Search Engine</strong> — MCTS + evolutionary; cada nó tem memory operator (inherit parent trajectory, escape local optima, etc.)</li><li><strong>Retrieval-Augmented Knowledge Base</strong> — hierarchical, platform-specific (architecture details, optimization guidance, debugging). <strong>Self-evolving &quot;skill library&quot;</strong> — sucessos viram knowledge para sessões futuras → &quot;in-context reinforcement learning&quot; sem retreinar LLM base</li><li><strong>Automated Evaluation Framework</strong> — TritonBench + PyTorch Profiler + NCU + Proton + MTIA Insight. Compiler-centric: MLIR-level instrumentation, profiling passes, structured trace synthesis. <strong>Sees WHY a bottleneck exists</strong> (memory-bound, compute-bound, occupancy-limited)</li><li><strong>Shared Data Foundation</strong> — sessões futuras herdam learnings. Compounding effect.</li><li><strong>Agentic Reinforcement Learning</strong> — agentic trajectories viram training data → post-train smaller specialized models → flywheel onde modelos melhores produzem kernels melhores em fewer search steps. <strong>Permite Meta self-host modelos eficientes em scale</strong>.</li></ol>\n<p><strong>O que isso destrava (capability nova):</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>Hardware proprietário (MTIA) sem documentação pública</strong>: encode arquitetura + ISA + optimization patterns no RAG → sistema gera kernels otimizados sem retreinamento. Resolve o problema &quot;LLM nunca foi treinado em MTIA&quot;</li><li><strong>Long tail de operators custom</strong> (tokenização, sequence truncation, fused features) — 80% dos production workloads que NÃO estão em cuBLAS/cuDNN</li><li><strong>Cross-platform</strong>: NVIDIA + AMD + MTIA + CPU em <strong>single system</strong> (vs separate prompt templates)</li><li><strong>Velocity</strong>: kernels que levavam <strong>semanas de expert engineering</strong> → <strong>horas de search/eval automatizado</strong></li></ul>\n<p><strong>Implicação estratégica para tese META:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>Hardware moat REAL e quantificado</strong>: 60% inference throughput improvement = direct ROI em capex efficiency</li><li><strong>MTIA productization destravada</strong>: KernelEvolve é o que permite Meta escalar MTIA em produção SEM exército de kernel engineers</li><li><strong>CapEx Meta gera ROI compounding</strong>: cada otimização melhora todos os modelos futuros (shared knowledge base)</li><li><strong>Diferenciação vs hyperscalers</strong>: GOOGL TPU compiler é mature mas focado em TPU only. AWS Trainium SDK + agentic ainda nascente. KernelEvolve cobre MULTIPLE hardware (incluindo NVDA), e é integrado ao stack de modelos de produção</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Cross-implications:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Para <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=CUDA\" title=\"_concepts/CUDA\">CUDA</a> — risco material ao moat de software NVDA. Ver seção &quot;Risk: AI-generated kernels&quot; lá.</li><li>Para <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MTIA\" title=\"_concepts/MTIA\">MTIA</a> — KernelEvolve é o destravador estrutural da MTIA produtiva</li><li>Para <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVDA\" title=\"wiki/NVDA\">NVDA</a> — ver seção &quot;Riscos / AI-generated kernels erodem CUDA moat&quot;</li><li>Para <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> — combina com Fubon (custom silicon +43x AVGO vs +20x NVDA wafer demand 2023-2027) — KernelEvolve é o mecanismo técnico que justifica o shift</li></ul>\n<h3>CP-SAT framing</h3>\n<p>Steiner descreve ad serving como <strong>Constraint Programming (CP-SAT) problem</strong>:</p>\n<ul><li>Maximizar valor total</li><li>Sujeito a: budget, latency, hardware availability</li><li>Resolvido em real-time por user, por request, billions of times/day</li></ul>\n<h3>Long-term + short-term reconciliation</h3>\n<p><strong>&quot;Anniversary Gift&quot; analogy</strong> (Steiner): amigo de 10 anos escolhe melhor presente que conhecido recente. Meta combina:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Long-term intent</strong>: 10 anos de history por usuário</li><li><strong>Short-term interest</strong>: o que clicaram nos últimos 10 segundos</li></ul>\n<p>Isso é o que TikTok não consegue replicar — TikTok tem real-time, mas falta long-term per-user history em escala.</p>\n<h3>&quot;The Creative is the Targeting&quot; — Advantage+ thesis</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Manual targeting está ficando obsoleto</strong></li><li><strong>Advantage+</strong> automatiza targeting completamente</li><li><strong>Job-to-be-done shifts</strong>: marketers param de &quot;tunar audiences&quot;, investem em <strong>creative quality</strong> (storytelling)</li><li>Meta faz mais dinheiro porque:<ol><li>Cobra por <strong>outcome</strong>, não targeting (advertiser ROAS)</li><li>Reduz <strong>friction</strong> de campanha setup</li><li>Captura <strong>upside</strong> em creative-driven matching</li></ol></li></ul>\n<h3>Implicações competitivas (resumo)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Competitor</th><th>Strength</th><th>Weakness vs Meta</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>TikTok</strong></td><td>Real-time signal</td><td>Falta long-term history em scale</td></tr><tr><td><strong>GOOGL</strong></td><td>Long-term intent (Search)</td><td>Sem real-time engagement loop</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Snap, Pinterest</strong></td><td>Niche audiences</td><td>Scale insuficiente para 1T param models economically</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Apple Pay/Amazon DSP</strong></td><td>First-party data</td><td>Não têm distribution multi-property + creative tools</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Implicações para <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a></h3>\n<ul><li><strong>CapEx Meta vai 100% para Ads/Inference ROI</strong> — não para &quot;speculative AI infra que talvez monetize&quot;</li><li>Diferenciado de <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=GOOGL\" title=\"wiki/GOOGL\">GOOGL</a> (CapEx serve GCP customers + Search + Workspace + DeepMind) e <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MSFT\" title=\"wiki/MSFT\">MSFT</a> (Azure + OpenAI + Copilot)</li><li>Meta <strong>internaliza 100% do retorno</strong> — cada dollar of CapEx → mais ad revenue per user</li><li><strong>Justifica</strong> os $115-135B FY26 CapEx: tem ROI direto e mensurável via revenue per user growth</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Management e governança</h2><p><em>Análise profunda na Pergunta 3.</em> Snapshot:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>CEO + Controlling Shareholder</strong>: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=mark-zuckerberg\" title=\"_people/mark-zuckerberg\">Mark Zuckerberg</a> — co-founder, controla empresa via shares classe B (&gt;50% voting power). Idade atual ~42 (nasceu 1984). <strong>Risk &amp; opportunity</strong> — histórico de &quot;private-company&quot; decisions (Metaverse, agora AI infra).</li><li><strong>CFO</strong>: Susan Li — desde 2022 como CFO (joined Meta 2008, ex-Morgan Stanley). ~$30M em equity. Voz analítica nas calls.</li><li><strong>CTO / Head of Reality Labs</strong>: Andrew Bosworth — criador do News Feed. ~$28M em equity.</li><li><strong>Board</strong>: 9 membros. Highlights: Marc Andreessen (a16z, respeitado VC), Peggy Alford (PayPal), Nancy Killefer, Drew Houston (Dropbox).</li><li><strong>Retorno ao acionista</strong>: Q4/25 <strong>NÃO teve buyback</strong> apesar de $81B em cash — sinal de conviction forte em reinvestimento interno. Dividend minúsculo.</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Track record de capital allocation de Zuckerberg</strong>:</p>\n<ul><li>✅ Instagram acquisition (2012, $1B) — home run</li><li>✅ WhatsApp acquisition (2014, $19B) — bom, monetização lenta mas começou</li><li>✅ &quot;Year of Efficiency&quot; (2023): layoff de 11k (20% headcount), stock 3x+ em 18m</li><li>❓ Reality Labs (2019-presente): $79B+ em prejuízos cumulativos, breakeven projetado ~2048</li><li>❓ AI CapEx bet (2025-): $72B FY25 + $115-135B FY26. Ainda em julgamento.</li></ul>\n<p>Padrão: Zuckerberg é <strong>decision-maker de alta conviction</strong>, faz bets grandes contra o consenso (&quot;must invest to compete&quot; vs &quot;proven ROI&quot;). Bet vs ATT (ad tracking) pós-2021: recuperou via AI recommendation — demonstrou capacidade de reagir e executar.</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Financeiros (snapshot)</h2><p><strong>FY25 vs FY24 — GAAP oficial (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-10-K\">10-K FY25</a>):</strong></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th>FY25</th><th>FY24</th><th>FY23</th><th>YoY (FY24→FY25)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Revenue</td><td>$200,966M</td><td>$164,501M</td><td>$134,902M</td><td>+22.2%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Cost of Revenue</strong></td><td><strong>$36,175M</strong></td><td><strong>$30,161M</strong></td><td><strong>$25,959M</strong></td><td><strong>+20%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Research and Development</td><td>$57,372M</td><td>$43,873M</td><td>$38,483M</td><td><strong>+31%</strong> (huge)</td></tr><tr><td>Marketing and Sales</td><td>$11,991M</td><td>$11,347M</td><td>$12,301M</td><td>+5.7%</td></tr><tr><td>General and Administrative</td><td>$12,152M</td><td>$9,740M</td><td>$11,408M</td><td>+24.8%</td></tr><tr><td>Total Costs and Expenses</td><td>$117,690M</td><td>$95,121M</td><td>$88,151M</td><td>+23.7%</td></tr><tr><td>Net income GAAP</td><td><strong>$60,460M</strong></td><td>$62,360M</td><td>$39,098M</td><td><strong>-3%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>EPS GAAP</td><td><strong>$23.49</strong></td><td>$23.86</td><td>$14.87</td><td>-1.6%</td></tr><tr><td>Effective tax rate</td><td><strong>30%</strong></td><td>12%</td><td>17%</td><td>+18 pts (OBBBA hit)</td></tr><tr><td>FCF</td><td>$43,585M</td><td>$52,103M</td><td>—</td><td>-16.4%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>CapEx (incl finance leases)</strong></td><td><strong>$72.22B</strong></td><td>$39,225M</td><td>—</td><td><strong>+84.1%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Q1 FY26 actuals — vs guide e YoY</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">Q1 FY26 earnings call</a>):</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th>Q1 FY26</th><th>Guide</th><th>YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Total revenue</strong></td><td><strong>$56.3B</strong></td><td>$53.5-56.5B (high end)</td><td><strong>+33%</strong> (+29% constant currency)</td></tr><tr><td>↳ FoA ad revenue</td><td>$55.0B</td><td>—</td><td>+33% (+29% cc)</td></tr><tr><td>↳ FoA other revenue</td><td>$885M</td><td>—</td><td>+74% (WhatsApp paid messaging + subs)</td></tr><tr><td>↳ Reality Labs</td><td>$402M</td><td>—</td><td>-2% (Quest weakness, AI Glasses up)</td></tr><tr><td>Ad impressions</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>+19%</td></tr><tr><td>Price per ad</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td><strong>+12%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Total expenses</td><td>$33.4B</td><td>—</td><td>+35%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Operating income</strong></td><td><strong>$22.9B</strong></td><td>—</td><td><strong>41% margin</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Tax rate (reported)</td><td><strong>-23%</strong></td><td>—</td><td>$8.3B benefit ✱</td></tr><tr><td>Tax rate (absent benefit)</td><td>14%</td><td>13-16% range</td><td>dentro do guide</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Net income GAAP</strong></td><td><strong>$26.8B</strong></td><td>—</td><td>EPS $10.44</td></tr><tr><td>Net income absent tax benefit</td><td>$18.7B</td><td>—</td><td>EPS adj $7.31</td></tr><tr><td><strong>CapEx Q1</strong></td><td><strong>$19.8B</strong></td><td>—</td><td>servers + DC + network</td></tr><tr><td><strong>FCF Q1</strong></td><td><strong>$12.4B</strong></td><td>—</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Cash + securities (Mar/26)</td><td>$81.2B</td><td>—</td><td>vs $81.6B Dec/25</td></tr><tr><td>Long-term debt (Mar/26)</td><td>$58.7B</td><td>—</td><td>vs $58.74B Dec/25</td></tr><tr><td>Headcount</td><td>77,900</td><td>—</td><td>-1% QoQ; further reduction May</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>✱ <strong>Tax benefit Q1 FY26</strong>: $8.3B benefit reflete updated US Treasury guidance (Feb/2026) sobre tax treatment of previously capitalized R&amp;D — partial relief do $15.93B noncash tax charge da Q3 2025.</p>\n<p><strong>Contractual commitments — Q1 FY26 update</strong>:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Data</th><th>Total commitments</th><th>$ Step-up</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Dec 2024</td><td>$32.8B</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Dec 2025</td><td>$131.05B</td><td>+$98B (FY25 inteiro)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Mar 2026 (implícito)</strong></td><td><strong>~$238B</strong></td><td><strong>+$107B em Q1 FY26 sozinho</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Driver Q1: &quot;<strong>multiyear cloud deals + infrastructure purchase agreements</strong>&quot; — cloud capacity coming online &quot;course of this year and 2027&quot;.</p>\n<blockquote>Nota: o recap do Paulo (Mar/2025) reportava <strong>adjusted</strong> numbers (EPS $29.08, Net Margin Adj 37.3%) — esses excluíam o hit do <strong>One Big Beautiful Bill Act (OBBBA)</strong> que elevou a tax rate pra 30% em FY25. Sem OBBBA, tax rate seria <strong>13%</strong> e EPS GAAP seria ~$29 (recap). Para comparar com FY24 apples-to-apples, use adjusted.</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Resultado SBC FY25</strong> (Note do 10-K): $20.43B total — $17.49B só em R&amp;D (85% do SBC total).</p>\n<p><strong>Explicação oficial do +20% em COGS</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-10-K\">10-K FY25</a> linha 957): <em>&quot;The increase was mainly due to higher operational expenses related to our data centers and technical infrastructure, which <strong>included decreases in the depreciation growth rate due to an extension in the useful lives of servers and network assets, effective January 1, 2025</strong>.&quot;</em> → Sem o life extension de servers, COGS teria crescido MAIS que 20% (o ajuste reduziu D&amp;A em ~$2.9B no ano).</p>\n<p><strong>FY26 CapEx guide</strong>: $115-135B (mais um +60-90% YoY). Se LG Model estiver certo: FCF vai pra <strong>-$8.7B em FY26</strong> (primeira vez FCF negativo na história pública da META).</p>\n<p><strong>Track record histórico (FY18-FY23 CAGRs)</strong>:</p>\n<ul><li>Revenue CAGR: +19%</li><li>Net income CAGR: +11%</li><li>FCF margin média: 30%</li><li>ROIC após tax: 21%</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Retorno do papel (anualizado, 6.9Y desde Mar-2019)</strong>:</p>\n<ul><li>Meta return: +21.9%</li><li>Fox IRR (posição Paulo): +20.1% (-1.8pp alpha — devido a timing, não tese)</li><li>Em 2025 isolado: Fox IRR +42.1% vs Meta +13.1% → <strong>+29pp alpha em 2025</strong></li></ul>\n<p><strong>Balanço / liquidez (Dec 31, 2025 — <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-10-K\">10-K FY25</a>):</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>Cash + marketable securities: $81.59B</strong></li><li><strong>Long-term debt: $58.74B</strong> (+~$22B YoY — grande bond issuance em 2025 pra financiar CapEx)</li><li>Senior unsecured notes maturam 2027-2064; interest obligations $2.98B short-term + $56.74B long-term</li><li><strong>Contractual commitments: $131.05B</strong> (vs $32.8B FY24 — +4x)</li><li>Non-marketable equity investments: <strong>$27.5B</strong> (vs $6.1B FY24) — salto via Scale AI $13.80B + Jio $5.82B</li><li>Share repurchases FY25: <strong>$26.26B</strong> (40M ações retired); dividends $5.32B</li><li>$25.03B remaining authorized pra buybacks</li><li>Headcount: <strong>78,865</strong> (+6% YoY)</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Third-party cloud spending (resposta à pergunta de 21-Apr-2026)</h2><p>Esta seção responde diretamente &quot;como evoluíram os gastos com cloud/neoclouds FY23-25 e como é alocado no P&amp;L&quot;. Confirmação oficial do <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-10-K\">10-K FY25</a>.</p>\n<h3>Contractual commitments — explodiu em 2025</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Data</th><th>Total commitments</th><th>Descrição oficial</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>31-Dec-2024</td><td><strong>$32.82B</strong></td><td>&quot;primarily related to our investments in servers and network infrastructure, and content costs&quot;</td></tr><tr><td>31-Dec-2025</td><td><strong>$131.05B</strong> (+$98B, <strong>4x YoY</strong>)</td><td><strong>&quot;mostly related to third-party cloud capacity arrangements</strong>, and our continued investments in servers and network infrastructure, data centers, and consumer hardware products in Reality Labs&quot;</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Schedule FY25 (Note 11 do 10-K):</strong></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Ano</th><th>$M</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>2026</td><td>30,634</td></tr><tr><td>2027</td><td>22,166</td></tr><tr><td>2028</td><td>21,221</td></tr><tr><td>2029</td><td>19,761</td></tr><tr><td>2030</td><td>19,407</td></tr><tr><td>Thereafter</td><td>~17,860</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td><strong>131,049</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Separadamente: <strong>~$25B em renewable energy commitments</strong> multi-year (FY24 number; FY25 provavelmente maior).</p>\n<h3>Como aparece no P&amp;L</h3>\n<p>Confirmação do <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a> (Item 7):</p>\n<blockquote><strong>&quot;Cost of revenue</strong> ... expenses related to the operation of our data centers and technical infrastructure, such as <strong>depreciation expense from servers, network infrastructure and buildings</strong>, employee compensation ... energy and bandwidth costs ... partner arrangements ... content costs.&quot;</blockquote>\n<blockquote><strong>&quot;Research and development</strong> ... employee compensation ... <strong>infrastructure costs</strong>; RL technology development costs; and facilities-related costs.&quot;</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Alocação:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Origem do gasto</th><th>Onde cai no P&amp;L</th><th>Mecanismo</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Data center <strong>próprio</strong> (CapEx)</td><td>COGS (maioria via D&amp;A) e R&amp;D</td><td>Capitalizado → depreciado ao longo de useful life (estendida Jan/25)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Third-party cloud</strong> (CoreWeave, Oracle, AWS etc.)</td><td>COGS (serving inference) <strong>ou</strong> R&amp;D (training / AI research)</td><td>Expensed no período; <strong>não é CapEx, não depreciado pela Meta</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Energy / bandwidth</td><td>COGS</td><td>Expensed</td></tr><tr><td>Content costs</td><td>COGS</td><td>Expensed (license costs)</td></tr><tr><td>Infrastructure R&amp;D</td><td>R&amp;D</td><td>Expensed diretamente</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Gap de disclosure</strong>: o 10-K NÃO separa &quot;third-party cloud&quot; como linha de expense. Fica embutido em COGS + R&amp;D. <strong>Só os COMMITMENTS futuros são disclosed</strong> ($131B).</p>\n<h3>Trajetória implícita de cloud/infra spend</h3>\n<ul><li>COGS <strong>+20% em FY25</strong> (de $30.2B pra $36.2B) <strong>mesmo com life extension reduzindo D&amp;A growth rate em ~$2.9B</strong> → sem o ajuste, seria ~+30%+</li><li>R&amp;D <strong>+31% em FY25</strong> (de $43.9B pra $57.4B) — maior salto histórico, absorve tanto AI infra quanto SBC ($17.5B só em R&amp;D SBC FY25)</li><li>Commitments <strong>+$98B em um ano</strong> (cloud capacity arrangements é a linha dominante)</li></ul>\n<p>Estimativa razoável: <strong>cloud + infra opex cresceu &gt;25-30% em FY25</strong>, divididos entre COGS e R&amp;D. Magnitude absoluta entre os dois provavelmente $15-25B (incluindo D&amp;A + third-party cloud + energy + content costs).</p>\n<p>Para número exato, precisaria:</p>\n<ul><li>Proxy FY25 (DEF 14A) — pode ter breakdown por categoria</li><li>Earnings calls Q4 FY25 — guidance / commentary</li><li>Pergunta direta pra IR</li></ul>\n<h3>Cross-links</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> — Meta é um dos 5 top hyperscalers; ver números atualizados lá</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVDA\" title=\"wiki/NVDA\">NVDA</a> — beneficiário direto; cita Meta GEM como prova de AI CapEx ROI</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AMZN\" title=\"wiki/AMZN\">AMZN</a> — AWS é um dos provedores prováveis de third-party cloud pra Meta</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MTIA\" title=\"_concepts/MTIA\">MTIA</a> — ASIC próprio da Meta; reduz dependência de cloud externa ao longo do tempo</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Modelagem COGS FY26</h2><p>Framework pra projetar COGS FY26 dado os $131B em novos commitments e dinâmica de D&amp;A. Criado em 2026-04-21 a partir do <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-10-K\">10-K FY25</a> Note 6 (P&amp;E) e Note 11 (commitments).</p>\n<h3>Composição de COGS FY25 (bottom-up — estimado)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Componente FY25</th><th>$B</th><th>Fonte</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>D&amp;A total P&amp;E</strong></td><td><strong>$18.00</strong></td><td>Note 6 (oficial)</td></tr><tr><td>↳ Servers + network specifically</td><td><strong>$13.36</strong></td><td>Note 6 (oficial)</td></tr><tr><td>↳ Buildings + outros</td><td>$4.64</td><td>derivado</td></tr><tr><td>Total lease costs (op + fin + variable)</td><td>$4.53</td><td>Note 7 (oficial)</td></tr><tr><td>↳ ~80% aloca em COGS</td><td>~$3.6</td><td>estimativa</td></tr><tr><td>Operations team comp + SBC</td><td>~$4-5</td><td>estimativa</td></tr><tr><td>Energy + bandwidth</td><td>~$3-4</td><td>estimativa</td></tr><tr><td>Partner arrangements (TAC + fees)</td><td>~$4-5</td><td>estimativa</td></tr><tr><td>Third-party cloud (opex purchased)</td><td>~$3-4</td><td>estimativa (base baixa pré-2025)</td></tr><tr><td>RL inventory + content costs</td><td>~$4-5</td><td>estimativa</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total COGS FY25</strong></td><td><strong>$36.18</strong></td><td>oficial</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Método 1 — Bottom-up por driver</h3>\n<p><strong>Driver 1: D&amp;A servers + network</strong> ($13.36B FY25 oficial)</p>\n<ul><li>Base servers + network: $98B gross FY25 (vs $68B FY24, <strong>+43% YoY</strong>)</li><li>CIP $50.5B em Dec/25 — pipeline entra em service 2026-27</li><li>CapEx FY26 guide $115-135B (midpoint $125B); ~65-70% vai pra servers + network (~$85B)</li><li>Useful life 5.5 anos; assuming mid-year in-service: adiciona ~$15-18B à base depreciável média em 2026</li><li><strong>FY26E: $17-19B</strong> (+$4-6B YoY)</li><li>⚠️ <strong>NÃO repete</strong> o one-time benefit de ~$2.9B da useful life extension (vento contra em 2026)</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Driver 2: D&amp;A buildings (data centers)</strong> (~$3B FY25)</p>\n<ul><li>CIP parcial + novos DCs coming online</li><li><strong>FY26E: $4-5B</strong> (+$1-2B)</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Driver 3: Third-party cloud opex em COGS</strong> (~$3-4B FY25 — wildcard)</p>\n<ul><li>Commitments de $30.6B vencem em 2026 (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a> Note 11)</li><li>Estimativa: 60-70% é third-party cloud = $18-21B total</li><li>Split 50-60% COGS / 40-50% R&amp;D (inference vs training — <strong>Meta tem discretion</strong>)</li><li><strong>FY26E COGS portion: $9-13B</strong> (+$6-9B — step-up material)</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Driver 4: Leases allocated to COGS</strong> ($3.6B FY25 → ~$4.5-5.5B FY26, +$1-2B)</p>\n<p><strong>Driver 5: Energy + bandwidth</strong> ($3-4B → $5-7B; nuclear Vistra + Louisiana ramping, +$2-3B)</p>\n<p><strong>Driver 6: Operations comp + partner arrangements + RL + content</strong> (scale com revenue +15-20% → +$2-3B)</p>\n<p><strong>Bottom-up total FY26E COGS: $47-54B</strong></p>\n<h3>Método 2 — Top-down ratio</h3>\n<p>Trajetória histórica:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Ano</th><th>COGS</th><th>Revenue</th><th>COGS/Rev</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>FY23</td><td>$26.0B</td><td>$134.9B</td><td><strong>19.2%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>FY24</td><td>$30.2B</td><td>$164.5B</td><td><strong>18.3%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>FY25</td><td>$36.2B</td><td>$201.0B</td><td><strong>18.0%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Por que o ratio deveria SUBIR em 2026</strong> (não continuar caindo):</p>\n<ul><li>FY25 teve tailwind não-recorrente: useful life extension ($2.9B benefit). Não repete.</li><li>Third-party cloud opex FY26 materializa em volume pela primeira vez.</li><li>LG Model do Paulo projeta operating margin 41.4% → 36% em FY26 (compressão de 540bps, distribuída entre COGS e R&amp;D).</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Sensitivity por cenário de Revenue FY26:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Cenário Revenue FY26</th><th>COGS 19.0%</th><th>COGS 20.0%</th><th>COGS 21.0%</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>$240B (conservador, +19%)</td><td>$45.6</td><td>$48.0</td><td>$50.4</td></tr><tr><td><strong>$260B (base, +29%)</strong></td><td><strong>$49.4</strong></td><td><strong>$52.0</strong></td><td><strong>$54.6</strong></td></tr><tr><td>$280B (bull, +39%)</td><td>$53.2</td><td>$56.0</td><td>$58.8</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Recomendação</h3>\n<p><strong>COGS FY26E: $48-54B</strong> (+32% a +49% YoY), <strong>ratio 19-21%</strong> de revenue.</p>\n<p>Ambos os métodos convergem nesse range. Gross margin FY26E ~<strong>79-81%</strong> (vs 82.0% FY25).</p>\n<h3>✅ Calibração oficial vs guidance Q4 FY25 call (28-Jan-2026) — atualizado pós-Q1 FY26</h3>\n<p>Após leitura do <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-Q4-earnings-call\">FY25-Q4-earnings-call</a> e refresh do <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">Q1 FY26 call (29-Apr-2026)</a>, Susan Li disclosed guidance oficial FY26. Cross-check:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th>Nosso modelo</th><th>Q4 FY25 guidance</th><th><strong>Q1 FY26 update</strong></th><th>Delta</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>CapEx FY26</td><td>$115-135B</td><td>$115-155B (per wiki ⚠️)</td><td><strong>$125-145B</strong></td><td><strong>Lower bound +$10B</strong> (Susan referencia &quot;prior $115-135B&quot; — ver discrepância wiki)</td></tr><tr><td>Total expenses FY26</td><td>— (só COGS)</td><td>$162-169B</td><td><strong>$162-169B (UNCHANGED)</strong></td><td>apesar de CapEx subir, opex não mexe</td></tr><tr><td>Tax rate FY26</td><td>—</td><td>13-16% (absent changes)</td><td><strong>13-16% confirmado</strong> (Q1 ex-benefit foi 14%)</td><td>OBBBA one-time confirmado</td></tr><tr><td>Revenue Q1 FY26</td><td>—</td><td>$53.5-56.5B guide</td><td><strong>$56.3B actual</strong> (high end)</td><td>beat</td></tr><tr><td>Revenue Q2 FY26</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td><strong>$58-61B guide</strong> (+23-30% YoY, +21-28% cc)</td><td>acelerando</td></tr><tr><td>Driver #1 expense growth</td><td>third-party cloud</td><td>&quot;infrastructure costs incl 3rd party cloud&quot; ✓</td><td>&quot;<strong>memory pricing component cost</strong>&quot; novo driver (CapEx)</td><td>adicionado</td></tr><tr><td>Operating income FY26</td><td>—</td><td>&quot;above 2025&quot;</td><td><strong>&quot;above 2025&quot; UNCHANGED</strong></td><td>confirmado</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>⚠️ <strong>Discrepância CapEx Q4 FY25</strong>: Wiki nota original (line 96 do Q4 MD) registra $115-155B; Q1 FY26 call refers to &quot;prior $115-135B&quot;. Possíveis causas: (a) OCR error no Q4 vision pipeline, (b) Susan misspoke. <strong>Tratamento</strong>: usar Q1 FY26 explicit ($125-145B) como canônico FY26 working number.</p>\n<p><strong>Reconciliação COGS dentro do $162-169B total expenses</strong>:</p>\n<ul><li>Se total expenses FY26 = $165B (midpoint), e assumindo R&amp;D continue growth +20% (de $57.4B pra $69B) + M&amp;S $13B + G&amp;A $14B = $96B non-COGS</li><li><strong>COGS implícito ≈ $165B - $96B = ~$69B</strong> (?? isso sobe nossa projeção)</li></ul>\n<p>Ou alternativa: se R&amp;D continue +31% trajetória FY25 = $75B, e M&amp;S+G&amp;A $27B → non-COGS = $102B → <strong>COGS implícito ~$63B</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>⚠️ Guidance oficial sugere COGS FY26 substancialmente ACIMA do nosso range $48-54B.</strong> Mais próximo de <strong>$58-68B (ratio 22-26%)</strong>. Razões prováveis:</p>\n<ol><li>Third-party cloud scaling rápido (Susan explicit)</li><li>Capacity constraint → Meta pagando premium por cloud/compute</li><li>Mix COGS vs R&amp;D pode ter shift — nossa premissa de 50-60% cloud spend em COGS pode estar baixa</li></ol>\n<p><strong>Recomendação atualizada (pós-guidance): COGS FY26E $55-68B (ratio 22-26%)</strong> — material step-up vs FY25 18.0%.</p>\n<p><strong>Sanity check Revenue FY26E</strong>: Q1 guide $53.5-56.5B × 4 quarters com acceleration sazonal (Q4 &gt; Q1 em ~1.3x historically) → full year FY26 pode chegar a <strong>$235-260B</strong>. COGS 22-26% × $250B = <strong>$55-65B</strong> ← converge com bottom-up revised.</p>\n<p><strong>🆕 Refresh pós-Q1 FY26 actuals (29-Apr-2026)</strong>:</p>\n<ul><li>Q1 FY26 actual: <strong>$56.3B</strong> (high end do guide) — +33% YoY, <strong>acelerou vs FY25 +22%</strong> (price/ad +12% vs +9% FY25)</li><li>Q2 FY26 guide: <strong>$58-61B</strong> → midpoint $59.5B = <strong>+27% YoY</strong></li><li>Trajetória: Q1 $56.3B + Q2 $59.5B + Q3 $61-65B + Q4 $66-70B (sazonal) → <strong>FY26 full year $243-260B</strong></li><li>COGS 22-26% × $250B = <strong>$55-65B</strong> — mantido</li><li><strong>Q1 FY26 expenses run-rate</strong>: $33.4B × 4 = $133.6B annualized; FY26 guide $162-169B → <strong>2H ramp material</strong> ($30B+ extras)</li></ul>\n<h3>Capacity constraint (dado qualitativo-chave da call)</h3>\n<p>Susan (Q&amp;A Eric Sheridan): <strong>&quot;we still expect to be capacity constrained through the course of 2026 until we complete the buildout that we have underway&quot;</strong></p>\n<p>Implicação: demand &gt; supply mesmo no patamar de $155B CapEx. Signal bullish — não é overbuild.</p>\n<p><strong>Q1 FY26 follow-up reaffirmation</strong> (Susan to Michael Nathanson): <em>&quot;I would be the first person to say we&#x27;ve underestimated our compute demand in the past, and I think we&#x27;ll get more visibility to the compute needs that we require to support our AI products as we launch them. So, right now, we&#x27;re also, in some sense, also planning for the future and planning to give ourselves the ability to scale inference capacity as product usage necessitates it ... I&#x27;m not sure there&#x27;s a team at the company that wouldn&#x27;t like to get a little more compute right now.&quot;</em></p>\n<p>→ Signal: capacity constraint não é só training, é <strong>inference scaling pra produtos</strong>. &quot;Planning for the future&quot; implícito → 2027 step-up.</p>\n<h3>🆕 Macro headwind — Iran conflict (revelado no Q1 FY26 follow-up)</h3>\n<p>Susan (resposta a Deepak Mathivanan, Cantor): <em>&quot;We did see <strong>reduction in advertiser spend coinciding with the beginning of the conflict in Iran at the end of February</strong>, and that continued through the quarter. We saw the <strong>most pronounced impact within the Middle East user region</strong>, but we also saw <strong>some softer trends in markets outside the Middle East, including in the U.S. and Western Europe</strong>.&quot;</em></p>\n<ul><li><strong>First explicit macro headwind disclosure</strong> em mais de um ano de calls</li><li><strong>Impact em Q1 FY26 já incorporado</strong> no $56.3B (que ainda assim fez beat at high end)</li><li><strong>Improvement in April</strong> — Susan disclosed</li><li><strong>Q2 guide ($58-61B)</strong> &quot;embeds a range of possible macro outcomes ranging from continued improvement to macro deceleration&quot; → sinaliza <strong>wider-than-usual spread</strong> no Q2 guide</li><li>Implicação modelagem: se April rebound não sustentar, ad revenue Q2 fica perto do low end do guide ($58B = +23% YoY); se sustentar, perto do top ($61B = +30% YoY)</li></ul>\n<h3>🆕 Cloud capacity strategy explícita (Chad Heaton, Q1 FY26 follow-up)</h3>\n<p>Pergunta Deepak Mathivanan (Cantor): &quot;compute capacity entre first party e third party, beyond near-term availability&quot;.</p>\n<p>Chad: <em>&quot;we&#x27;re contracting capacity from a number of third-party cloud providers to meet our infrastructure needs. These are <strong>multi-year contracts that will come online progressively over the course of 2026 and 2027</strong>, and the capacity will primarily support <strong>AI workloads</strong>. We still anticipate investing significantly in our owned and leased data center capacity. However, <strong>a lot of that is going to be for capacity that comes online in future years</strong>. So, we&#x27;ve been signing cloud deals that will enable us to bring capacity online <strong>more quickly this year and next year</strong>.&quot;</em></p>\n<p><strong>Implicações pra modelagem</strong>:</p>\n<ol><li><strong>Third-party cloud = bridge solution 2026-27</strong>: Meta usa porque DCs próprios demoram a entrar em operação</li><li><strong>DC próprios = peso 2027+</strong>: o ramp atual de CapEx ($125-145B FY26) está construindo capacity que <strong>não monetiza no mesmo ano</strong> — deprecia depois</li><li><strong>Workload split implícito</strong>: third-party = &quot;AI workloads&quot; (training + inference fungível); first-party DCs = production serving + future scale</li><li><strong>OpEx puts/takes</strong> (Susan): &quot;<em>A big one, frankly, is the timing of cloud deals coming online and when the capacity gets delivered</em>&quot; → <strong>timing risk material no expense outlook FY26</strong> ($162-169B range é wide por isso)</li><li><strong>Restructuring offset</strong>: workforce reduction savings em FY26 são <strong>integralmente offset por restructuring costs intra-year</strong> (Susan: &quot;lower going forward employee compensation expense ... offset within this year by restructuring costs&quot;). Net OpEx unchanged.</li></ol>\n<h3>🆕 Compute ROI A/B test (Q3 FY25 disclosed)</h3>\n<p>Mark em Q3 FY25 (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q3-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-Q3-earnings-call\">FY25-Q3-earnings-call</a>): <strong>&quot;We&#x27;ve done A/B tests showing that every dollar of incremental compute added to AI recommendation systems is generating significantly more than a dollar of revenue.&quot;</strong></p>\n<p>Isso é a evidência quantitativa que validou o CapEx ramp. Transformou narrativa:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Q1 FY25</strong>: &quot;we must invest to compete&quot; (strategic necessity)</li><li><strong>Q3 FY25</strong>: &quot;every $1 compute &gt; $1 revenue&quot; (proven ROI)</li><li><strong>Q4 FY25</strong>: $115-155B CapEx justificado por esse framework</li></ul>\n<h3>Depreciation trajectory — Susan explicit Q3</h3>\n<p>Susan (Q3 FY25 Q&amp;A Doug Anmuth, JPM): <em>&quot;Depreciation expense will continue accelerating through 2026&quot;</em> — valida nossa projeção bottom-up de COGS FY26 em $55-68B (D&amp;A é driver dominante).</p>\n<h3>Capital returns evolution FY25 (sinal de priorização)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Quarter</th><th>Buybacks</th><th>Dividends</th><th>Total</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Q1 FY25</td><td>$13.4B</td><td>$1.3B</td><td>$15.4B (2 meses de FY25 adjusted)</td></tr><tr><td>Q2 FY25</td><td>$9.8B</td><td>$1.3B</td><td>$11B</td></tr><tr><td>Q3 FY25</td><td>$3.2B</td><td>$1.3B</td><td>$4.5B ⬇️</td></tr><tr><td>Q4 FY25</td><td>$1.4B</td><td>$2.0B</td><td>$3.4B ⬇️</td></tr><tr><td><strong>FY25 total</strong></td><td><strong>$27.8B</strong></td><td><strong>$5.9B</strong></td><td><strong>$33.7B</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Tendência</strong>: capital return trajectory em queda sharp ao longo de FY25. Buyback drop de $13.4B (Q1) pra $1.4B (Q4) = <strong>-90% em 12 meses</strong>. Meta priorizando reinvestimento em AI.</p>\n<p><strong>Implicação pra modelagem</strong>: não assumir buybacks agressivos em FY26. EPS boost via shrinking shares provavelmente modesto. Mark quote Q4: &quot;highest order priority is investing our resources to position ourselves as a leader in AI.&quot;</p>\n<h3>Gotchas que podem quebrar o modelo</h3>\n<ol><li><strong>Mix COGS vs R&amp;D</strong>: Meta tem discretion em alocação. Em FY25, R&amp;D cresceu +31% vs COGS +20% — ela preferiu alocar AI spend em R&amp;D. Se continuar, COGS/rev sobe menos mas R&amp;D/rev sobe mais. <strong>Total spend é o que importa; Gross Margin isolado pode enganar.</strong></li><li><strong>Timing of CIP placement into service</strong>: se Meta segura itens em CIP mais tempo, D&amp;A 2026 vem menor (empurra pra 2027). Earnings calls vão detalhar.</li><li><strong>Parte dos $131B commitments NÃO é cloud opex</strong> — alguns são POs de servers (vira CapEx → deprecia depois, não hit direto em 2026 COGS).</li><li><strong>Renewable energy commitments ($25B+)</strong> são PPAs, hit COGS conforme consumo — multi-year distribution.</li><li><strong>Revenue growth real</strong> vs guide: se FY26 decepciona em revenue, ratio COGS/rev sobe mecanicamente.</li><li><strong>Capitalized interest subindo</strong> ($535M FY25 vs $384M FY24, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a> Note 6): parte do custo de financiar bonds está indo pro P&amp;E capitalizado (vira D&amp;A depois) em vez de cair em interest expense imediato.</li></ol>\n<h3>Dados-fonte pra refinar</h3>\n<ul><li>[x] <strong>Q4 FY25 earnings call transcript</strong> (Jan/2026) — ✅ ingerido <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-Q4-earnings-call\">FY25-Q4-earnings-call</a></li><li>[x] <strong>Q1 FY26 earnings call</strong> (29-Apr-2026) — ✅ ingerido <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call</a>; revenue beat, CapEx raised, +$107B commitments</li><li>[x] <strong>Q1 FY26 follow-up call (Q&amp;A com analistas)</strong> — ✅ ingerido 2026-04-30, ver <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY26-Q1-follow-up-call\">FY26-Q1-follow-up-call</a>; cloud strategy explicitada (multi-year third-party 2026-27 = bridge; owned/leased DCs = future years); macro Iran headwind disclosed; LPA Q2 &gt; Q1 confirmed; GenAI ad creative tools 8M advertisers + 3% conversion gain detalhado</li><li>[ ] <strong>Breakdown oficial dos $30.6B 2026 commitments</strong> entre cloud opex vs own infra POs — pergunta pra IR</li><li>[ ] <strong>Consensus de analistas</strong> pra Revenue/COGS FY26 — compare vs este framework</li><li>[ ] <strong>Manus deal disclosure</strong> — Susan Q1 FY26 deferred (&quot;still working through details&quot;) — acquisition material em pipeline? Q1 FY26 follow-up (29-Apr): analyst framing &quot;kind of getting undone&quot; — Susan reafirmou confidence em agentic roadmap mas continua sem detalhes. <strong>Status: aparentemente abortado ou reestruturado.</strong></li></ul>\n<h3>Cross-links</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=#Third-party cloud spending (novo — FY25 10-K disclosure)\" title=\"#Third-party cloud spending (novo — FY25 10-K disclosure)\">↑ Third-party cloud spending</a> — base factual do framework</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a> — Note 6 (P&amp;E), Note 7 (Leases), Note 11 (Commitments)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> — contexto macro</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Catalisadores</h2><ul><li><strong>Q1 FY26 revenue</strong>: ✅ <strong>$56.3B (high end do guide $53.5-56.5B)</strong> — beat. +33% YoY (+29% cc) acelerou vs FY25. Price/ad +12% (vs +9% FY25). Primeiro reality check pós-guidance positivo.</li><li><strong>Q2 FY26 guide</strong>: $58-61B (+23-30% YoY) — sequencial acelerando.</li><li><strong>Meta AI monetização</strong>: Q1 FY26 — Susan reconheceu publicamente que Business AIs vão estabelecer &quot;longer term monetization model&quot;; &quot;commission structures or premium offerings&quot; para personal agents. Ainda não monetizado.</li><li><strong>Reels CPM catch-up</strong>: 30-40% abaixo de Feed. Se fechar, tailwind material.</li><li><strong>FTC antitrust</strong>: <strong>Meta ganhou em Nov/2025</strong> (grande win — removeu existential US breakup risk).</li><li><strong>TikTok JV constraints</strong>: se JV limita inovação de ads TikTok, Meta se beneficia.</li><li><strong>WhatsApp monetization</strong>: CtoM TAM estimado $40B (Wolfe). Q1 FY26: Business AIs em WhatsApp expanded para LatAm + Indonésia; ads &amp; status com hundreds of millions of daily viewers.</li><li><strong>AI Glasses</strong>: tripling daily users YoY; new RayBan Optics (all-day wear) + Meta RayBan displays + neural band — &quot;consumer appetite for display glasses&quot;.</li><li><strong>Spark integration em recommender</strong>: Q1 FY26 mostrou +10% time spent FB, +8% video time global. Roadmap: &quot;first-principles understanding of what each piece of content is about&quot;.</li><li><strong>🆕 Meta AI Shopping mode</strong> (Q1 FY26 follow-up): powered by Muse Spark, lançado em standalone app + website (US only). Use cases ativos: product inspiration, browsing, comparisons. Roadmap = personalization + agentic capabilities for &quot;engaging commerce on your behalf&quot;. Susan: &quot;commerce has always been ... our largest ads vertical&quot; — <strong>adjacency strategy clara entre Meta AI shopping e o ad business</strong>.</li><li><strong>🆕 Threads + WhatsApp Status monetization rampa LENTA</strong>: Q1 FY26 follow-up — Susan baixou expectativas — Threads &quot;not meaningful driver of impression or revenue growth this year&quot;; WhatsApp Status &quot;not meaningful contributor to total impressions or revenue growth for the next few years&quot; (geo mix LatAm/Asia/Africa = lower ARPU + targeting menos robusto). Ar de catalisador desloca pra 2027+.</li><li><strong>🆕 Manus deal &quot;kind of getting undone&quot;</strong> (analyst framing, Q1 FY26 follow-up): Susan deferred details mas signal de que pipeline M&amp;A em agentic continua. Próximas acquisitions provavelmente ainda em 2026.</li><li><strong>🆕 Meta AI — três pilares para &quot;personal superintelligence&quot;</strong> (Q1 FY26 follow-up — Susan to Rich Greenfield Lightshed): Susan articulou explicitamente como Meta vai diferenciar Meta AI vs ChatGPT/Gemini/Claude num mundo agentic:<ol><li><strong>Social graph + first-party signals</strong> — <em>&quot;allow us to ground agents that we build into who you care about or what you follow, what you&#x27;ve engaged with. So that should get us to more personalized outcomes than generic assistance.&quot;</em> Vantagem direta de 3.56B Family DAP + histórico de engagement.</li><li><strong>Messaging como surface natural pra agents</strong> — <em>&quot;where people coordinate plans, where they already interact and transact with businesses.&quot;</em> WhatsApp/Messenger/IG DM = entry points pra Meta AI orquestrar tools (booking, shopping, commerce) sem fricção de app switch.</li><li><strong>Hardware (Ray-Ban Meta Glasses) = best form factor pra agentic</strong> — <em>&quot;hands-free, real-time, and I think over time it should become really proactive.&quot;</em> Justifica $19B/ano de Reality Labs losses como <strong>bet em form factor de próxima geração</strong> pra distribuir Meta AI.</li></ol></li></ul>\n<p>→ Framing estratégico importante: Meta NÃO compete com OpenAI no modelo per se (&quot;caught up to being in the pack in record time&quot; — Susan admit), compete na <strong>integração com surface (apps) + form factor (glasses) + grounding signal (social graph)</strong>. Decisivo pra avaliar bull case Meta AI vs hyperscaler peers que têm hardware/agents mas sem social graph nem messaging install base.</p>\n<ul><li><strong>🆕 &quot;Caught us up to being in the pack in record time&quot;</strong> — Susan caracterizou Muse Spark como milestone que <strong>fechou o gap com frontier</strong> (não tomou liderança ainda). Talent-dense lab + breakneck pace. <em>&quot;vast majority of the journey is ahead of us&quot;</em> — multimodal perception, tool use, multi-agent orchestration. Honest framing — não overpromise.</li></ul></section>\n<details class=\"notes-appendix\"><summary>Notas, pendências e changelog</summary><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Pontos em aberto / a investigar</h2><ul><li>[ ] <strong>10-K FY25</strong> não está no vault (SEC EDGAR bloqueou download nesta sessão — 403). Baixar manualmente do <a href=\"https://www.sec.gov/cgi-bin/browse-edgar?action=getcompany&amp;amp;CIK=0001326801&amp;amp;type=10-K\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">EDGAR</a> e colocar em <code>raw/META/sec/FY25-10-K.pdf</code>.</li><li>[ ] <strong>Últimas 4 earnings calls FY25</strong> (Q1-Q4): não estão no vault. Fontes: investor.fb.com ou seekingalpha.</li><li>[ ] <strong>Proxy FY25</strong> (DEF 14A): pra análise de governança + exec comp atual.</li><li>[ ] <strong>3 PDFs</strong> ficaram com status NEEDS_OCR (image-based): <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-02-ROIC-GEM-Now-LLMs-Later-AustinLyons\" title=\"raw-md/META/2025-02-ROIC-GEM-Now-LLMs-Later-AustinLyons\">2025-02-ROIC-GEM-Now-LLMs-Later-AustinLyons</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-03-Eye-of-the-Hurricane\" title=\"raw-md/META/2025-03-Eye-of-the-Hurricane\">2025-03-Eye-of-the-Hurricane</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-04-FTC-antitrust-case\" title=\"raw-md/META/2025-04-FTC-antitrust-case\">2025-04-FTC-antitrust-case</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-09-Recommender-Model-Evolution-FundaAI\" title=\"raw-md/META/2025-09-Recommender-Model-Evolution-FundaAI\">2025-09-Recommender-Model-Evolution-FundaAI</a>. Se quiser conteúdo, precisa OCR.</li><li>[ ] Detalhes de Meta Strategic Infrastructure (MSI), Meta Compute, AMD $100B deal — validar no 10-K FY25.</li><li>[ ] MTIA chip status e roadmap — quanto da carga de ML já roda em MTIA vs NVDA/AMD?</li><li>[ ] Fox price target atual e trajetória FY25 → FY26 na LG Model.</li></ul></section><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Histórico de atualizações</h2><ul><li><strong>2026-06-04</strong>: cross-ref <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/AVGO/FY26-Q2-earnings-call\">AVGO Q2 FY26 EC, 03-Jun-2026</a>. <strong>Datapoint META-side material</strong>: Hock Tan disclosa pela 1ª vez quantificação da <strong>partnership MTIA-Broadcom anunciada April 2026</strong>: &quot;<strong>3 gigawatts through end of 2028</strong>&quot;, com <strong>initial 1GW order received</strong> (XPUs + networking) e <strong>delivery H2 2027</strong>. Substitui a hipótese histórica &quot;Broadcom (a confirmar)&quot; para MTIA — agora confirmação institucional. <strong>Reconcilia com Q1 FY26 EC Meta</strong> que mencionava &quot;<strong>&gt;1GW custom silicon Broadcom + AMD + Nvidia</strong>&quot;: o &quot;1GW&quot; Susan Li referenciava era o <strong>initial order dentro do framework de 3GW</strong>. <strong>Magnitude revenue Broadcom-side</strong>: 3GW × $80M-$100M/GW ASP framing = <strong>$7-10B AVGO revenue MTIA-related until 2028</strong>. Cross-link <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MTIA\" title=\"_concepts/MTIA\">MTIA</a> (page atualizada com quantificação) + <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AVGO\" title=\"wiki/AVGO\">AVGO</a> seção &quot;Q2 FY26 EC&quot;. <strong>Implicação tese META</strong>: cost advantage estrutural em AI infra via MTIA passa de &quot;hipotético/in-house&quot; para &quot;quantified pipeline contratada&quot; com supplier institucional. Confirma direção multi-vendor (MTIA-AVGO + GPU NVDA + AMD + Graviton AWS) como estratégia operacional, não retórica.</li><li><strong>2026-05-27</strong>: cross-ref <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\">SemiAnalysis &amp;quot;Anthropic Growth and Bedrock Mix&amp;quot; 27-May-2026</a>. <strong>Datapoints META-side</strong>: (1) <strong>Pattern de upsell GCP-Meta confirmado</strong>: SemiAnalysis caracteriza GCP como &quot;plataforma para upsell adicional&quot; e cita Meta como exemplo paradigmático — <em>&quot;a large GPU deal that subsequently led to large-scale Gemini adoption, and then a massive TPU hardware deal.&quot;</em> Confirma trilha Meta-Google: cloud GPU → modelo Gemini → silicon TPU. (2) <strong>Meta como cliente Graviton material</strong>: AWS earnings call já tinha disclose (&quot;tens of millions of Graviton cores&quot; — abr/2026); SemiAnalysis reforça que <strong>Amazon agora tem large CPU + Graviton deals com Anthropic, OpenAI e Meta</strong>. Confirma Meta multi-cloud na camada CPU (não só own DC com <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MTIA\" title=\"_concepts/MTIA\">MTIA</a>). (3) <strong>Multi-vendor chip strategy materializada</strong>: Meta tem MTIA própria + GPU NVDA + Graviton AWS + TPU Google = stack diversificado. SemiAnalysis frame: &quot;no single chip architecture can serve every workload&quot; (Meta declarado em call anterior, agora validado pela alocação real). <strong>Implicação</strong>: tese Meta de &quot;decoupling compute supply via multi-vendor + own ASIC&quot; tem evidência concreta crescente. <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AMZN\" title=\"wiki/AMZN\">AMZN</a> / <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=GOOGL\" title=\"wiki/GOOGL\">GOOGL</a> / <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AVGO\" title=\"wiki/AVGO\">AVGO</a> também têm entradas cruzadas nessa data. Cross-link: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> (Meta = case study primário do &quot;ASIC + GPU coexistence&quot; no buy side).</li><li><strong>2026-04-20</strong>: wiki criada a partir da Fase 1 (3 10-Ks FY22/23/24, Paulo&#x27;s investment case Jan/2024, recap Mar/2025, follow-up Feb/2025, FundaAI recommender — 4 research pending OCR). Estado da tese = <code>posicao</code> per Paulo. Framework IWIKs #1-6 importado do recap.</li><li><strong>2026-04-20</strong>: refatorada para padrão Karpathy — extraídas entity pages <code><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MTIA\" title=\"_concepts/MTIA\">MTIA</a></code> e <code><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=mark-zuckerberg\" title=\"_people/mark-zuckerberg\">Mark Zuckerberg</a></code>. Linkada no <code><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=INDEX\" title=\"INDEX\">INDEX</a></code>.</li><li><strong>2026-04-21</strong>: <strong>10-K FY25 incorporado</strong> (baixado via curl do SEC EDGAR → HTML extraction pra <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a>). Atualizações materiais: (1) COGS FY25 oficial $36.2B (+20% YoY, mesmo com life extension reduzindo D&amp;A em $2.9B); (2) R&amp;D FY25 $57.4B (+31% YoY — maior salto histórico); (3) <strong>contractual commitments explodiram de $32.8B pra $131.05B em um ano, &quot;mostly related to third-party cloud capacity arrangements&quot;</strong>; (4) Net income GAAP $60.5B (EPS $23.49) vs adjusted $74.9B ($29.08) — diferença pelo hit OBBBA elevando tax rate de 13% implied pra 30% reportado; (5) Scale AI $13.80B minority investment closed FY25; (6) Louisiana data center JV co-development (Oct/25); (7) long-term debt cresceu +$22B ($37B→$59B); (8) adicionada nova seção &quot;Third-party cloud spending&quot; respondendo pergunta de 21-Apr.</li><li><strong>2026-04-21</strong>: adicionada seção <strong>&quot;Modelagem COGS FY26&quot;</strong> — framework bottom-up + top-down convergente em <strong>COGS FY26E $48-54B (ratio 19-21% de revenue)</strong>. Partiu da pergunta do Paulo sobre como projetar COGS dada a explosão de commitments de third-party cloud. Usou Note 6 (P&amp;E detail com D&amp;A servers+network de $13.36B FY25 e gross de $98B) + Note 11 (schedule dos $131B commitments, $30.6B vence 2026).</li><li><strong>2026-04-21</strong>: Paulo adicionou 2 pastas de transcripts: <code>Q&amp;A Transcript</code> (12 follow-up calls FY23-FY25) + <code>Call Transcripts</code> (4 earnings calls FY25). <strong>Todos os 16 PDFs são scan-based</strong> — pdftotext extrai &lt;25 chars. Copiados pra <code>raw/META/earnings-calls/</code> com convenção de nome, MDs criados com status NEEDS_OCR. Wiki não pôde ser atualizada com conteúdo dos calls até OCR ser feito. Fontes identificadas e listadas acima pra quando for destravado.</li><li><strong>2026-04-21</strong>: ✅ <strong>FY25-Q4 earnings call processado via Claude vision OCR</strong>. Pipeline implementado: <code>pip install --user pypdfium2 Pillow</code> (sem T.I.) → rasterize 21 páginas PNG → Read cada uma via Claude vision → síntese estruturada em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-Q4-earnings-call\">FY25-Q4-earnings-call</a>. <strong>Update material na seção Modelagem COGS FY26</strong>: guidance oficial CapEx <strong>$115-155B</strong> (upper bound +$20B vs nosso input), total expenses <strong>$162-169B</strong>, tax rate <strong>13-16%</strong>, Revenue Q1 <strong>$53.5-56.5B</strong>. Susan confirmou textualmente que &quot;third-party cloud spend&quot; é driver principal do expense growth. <strong>COGS FY26 revisado pra $55-68B</strong> (vs $48-54B original) baseado em reconciliação com total expenses guide.</li><li><strong>2026-04-21</strong>: ✅ <strong>Q1 + Q2 + Q3 FY25 earnings calls também processados</strong> via mesmo pipeline Claude vision OCR (57 páginas totais). Narrativa FY25 evolution mapeada: <strong>&quot;Year of Efficiency&quot; (Q1) → &quot;Path to Superintelligence&quot; (Q2, MSL created) → &quot;Compute ROI proven&quot; (Q3, A/B test) → &quot;Year of AI Acceleration&quot; (Q4)</strong>. Capital returns evolution significativa: Q1 $15.4B → Q2 $11B → Q3 $4.5B → Q4 $3.4B. <strong>Q3 FY25 disclosed compute ROI A/B test</strong>: &quot;every dollar incremental compute = significantly more than dollar of revenue&quot; — primeira evidência quantitativa pública validando CapEx ramp. Meta issued <strong>$25B bonds em Q3</strong> (primeira emissão material). OBBBA $18B valuation allowance hit concentrado em Q3. Cross-ticker data: Meta citou &quot;diversifying chip supply&quot; = reconhecimento oficial de <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MTIA\" title=\"_concepts/MTIA\">MTIA</a> + AMD deal.</li><li><strong>2026-04-23</strong>: 4 research PDFs + 12 follow-up calls FY23-FY25 destravados via rapidocr-onnxruntime pipeline (status NEEDS_OCR removido).</li><li><strong>2026-04-27</strong>: ingerido <strong>No Priors Episode 68 — Matt Steiner interview</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-No-Priors-Matt-Steiner-Meta-Ad-System\" title=\"raw-md/META/2026-No-Priors-Matt-Steiner-Meta-Ad-System\">2026-No-Priors-Matt-Steiner-Meta-Ad-System</a>). <strong>Adicionada nova seção &quot;Stack técnico de monetização — deep dive&quot;</strong> com arquitetura em 4 camadas (Andromeda → Lattice → GEM → Adaptive Ranking), hardware moat (custom NVDA Grace Hopper SKU + MTIA + KernelEvolve com 60-100% perf gain), e implicações competitivas. Insights novos: (a) Meta é <strong>co-designer de NVDA Grace Hopper SKU</strong> (não-trivial — não é commodity buyer); (b) <strong>Adaptive Ranking ~1T params em sub-second latency</strong> — diferenciação real-time vs competitors; (c) <strong>GEM lê visual/contextual</strong>, resposta direta ao Apple ATT 2021; (d) &quot;Anniversary Gift&quot; framing — Meta combina long-term history + short-term real-time signal, gap que TikTok não preenche; (e) <strong>CapEx Meta tem ROI direto</strong> (100% internalizado em Ads ROI), diferentemente de GOOGL/MSFT que servem cloud customers.</li><li><strong>2026-04-30</strong>: ✅ <strong>Q1 FY26 follow-up call ingerido</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY26-Q1-follow-up-call\">FY26-Q1-follow-up-call</a> — Susan Li + Chad Heaton em Q&amp;A, 29-Apr-2026). <strong>Updates materiais</strong>: (1) <strong>Macro headwind Iran</strong> disclosed — primeira vez em ciclos recentes Susan reconhece reduction em advertiser spend desde end of February (most pronounced Middle East mas softer trends US + W.Europe); April improvement; Q2 guide embeds wide range; (2) <strong>LPA Q2 &gt; Q1</strong> confirmado — rollout Q1 inteiro = full quarter impact em Q2+, Q2 outlook já incorpora; appeal segue em curso; (3) <strong>Threads 150M+ DAUs</strong> + ads em 200+ países — mas &quot;not meaningful driver&quot; FY26; priority verticals = NBA, K-pop, reality TV, US + Japan; (4) <strong>WhatsApp Status ads = hundreds of millions of viewers/dia</strong> — global rollout 2026 mas estrutural: monetiza ABAIXO de IG Stories (&quot;next few years&quot; pra ser meaningful) — geo mix LatAm/Ásia/África = lower ARPU + targeting menos robusto sem Meta Account Center linking; (5) <strong>GenAI ad-creative tools: 8M advertisers</strong> (vs 4M end of 2024 = 2x); SMBs maioria; <strong>video generation +3% conversion</strong> em large-scale test; features expandindo (image animation, video filters, music generation, voiceover translation, image overlay translation); (6) <strong>Cloud capacity strategy explícita</strong> (Chad): third-party multi-year contracts = bridge 2026-27 (online &quot;more quickly&quot;); owned/leased DCs = future years; primarily AI workloads; (7) <strong>OpEx puts/takes</strong>: workforce reduction savings offset by restructuring intra-FY26 → expense outlook unchanged; timing of cloud deals = big variable; (8) <strong>Compute reaffirmation</strong>: &quot;we&#x27;ve underestimated compute demand in past, will get more visibility... not sure there&#x27;s a team that wouldn&#x27;t like more compute&quot; — implícito 2027 step-up; (9) <strong>CapEx posture</strong>: &quot;we aren&#x27;t really optimizing for a specific cash flow level this year&quot; — confirmação de que FCF não é guardrail; (10) <strong>Meta AI Shopping mode</strong> powered by Muse Spark, US-only standalone app + website; product inspiration/browsing/comparisons; roadmap = personalization + agentic commerce; (11) <strong>Manus deal &quot;kind of getting undone&quot;</strong> (analyst framing) — Susan deferred mas reafirma confidence em agentic roadmap; (12) <strong>Meta AI cross-app integration ainda rudimentary</strong> (Gmail mentioned); 3 differentiators: social graph + first-party signals, messaging surface, Ray-Ban Meta Glasses como form factor; (13) Mark&#x27;s &quot;personal superintelligence&quot; framing reaffirmed. Wiki atualizada em: tese summary, IWIK #5 + #6, KPIs (Threads DAU, WhatsApp Status), drivers receita (GenAI advertisers), Riscos (estruturais + macro), Catalisadores (Shopping, Threads/Status caveat, Manus), Modelagem COGS (capacity constraint follow-up + macro Iran + cloud strategy + restructuring offset), pontos em aberto.</li><li><strong>2026-05-12</strong>: ⚠️ <strong>Q1 FY26 follow-up call re-ingestão (deep pass)</strong> — PDF original do call salvo em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-follow-up-call.pdf\" title=\"raw/META/earnings-calls/FY26-Q1-follow-up-call.pdf\">FY26-Q1-follow-up-call.pdf</a> (já estava em raw-md desde 30-Abr; agora source PDF também presente). Adicionados ao <strong>corpo da wiki</strong> (antes só em histórico): (a) <strong>Meta AI três pilares para personal superintelligence</strong> (social graph + messaging surface + Ray-Ban Glasses form factor) como nova entrada em Catalisadores — framing estratégico que Susan articulou para Rich Greenfield (Lightshed); (b) <strong>Meta AI Business Assistant</strong> disclosure (novo produto B2B pra advertisers otimizarem campaigns, adjacente aos ad-creative tools) — primeiro vetor explícito de Meta AI monetizando lado business; (c) <strong>&quot;Caught us up to being in the pack in record time&quot;</strong> framing — Susan honest admission sobre Muse Spark = fechou gap mas não tomou liderança, <em>&quot;vast majority of the journey is ahead&quot;</em> (multimodal perception, tool use, multi-agent orchestration). Drivers de receita atual atualizado com Meta AI Business Assistant como vetor B2B adjacente aos ad-creative tools.</li><li><strong>2026-04-29</strong>: ✅ <strong>Q1 FY26 earnings call ingerido</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call</a> — call do dia, processado a partir de Bloomberg Talk Transcript). <strong>Updates materiais</strong>: (1) Revenue Q1 FY26 <strong>$56.3B (+33% YoY)</strong> — high end do guide; (2) Price/ad <strong>+12% YoY</strong> (vs +9% FY25 inteiro) — eficiência AI accelerating; (3) <strong>CapEx FY26 raised pra $125-145B</strong> (driver: memory pricing + DC futuro), com discrepância vs wiki Q4 ($115-155B vs Susan referenciar &quot;prior $115-135B&quot;); (4) Total expenses FY26 <strong>unchanged</strong> $162-169B; (5) <strong>Contractual commitments +$107B em UM trimestre</strong> (multi-year cloud + IPAs) — implícito ~$238B em Mar/2026; (6) <strong>$8.3B tax benefit</strong> Q1 (US Treasury R&amp;D guidance Feb/2026) parcialmente alivia OBBBA hit Q3/25; (7) <strong>Headcount reduction May 2026</strong> anunciada (&quot;leaner operating model&quot;); (8) Q2 FY26 guide $58-61B (+23-30%); (9) Susan <strong>reconheceu publicamente &quot;we have continued to underestimate our compute needs&quot;</strong> — sinal implícito de step-up 2027; (10) <strong>Muse Spark released</strong> (primeiro modelo MSL, 10 meses do stand-up), Meta AI upgraded; (11) <strong>&gt;1GW custom silicon Broadcom</strong> + AMD chips + Nvidia — diversificação multi-vendor; (12) Spark integration showing recommender wins (+10% time FB, +8% video time global); (13) Adaptive ranking 1T params confirmed pela CFO; (14) <strong>&gt;$10B ARR creator partnerships ads (doubled YoY)</strong> + <strong>&gt;$20B ARR value optimization suite (doubled YoY)</strong> — vetores novos; (15) <strong>&gt;10M weekly biz AI conversations (10x YoY)</strong>; (16) <strong>Manus deal</strong> referenced — Susan deferred details. Wiki atualizada em: tese summary, IWIK #5, KPIs usuário, drivers receita, snapshot financeiro (nova tabela Q1 FY26), Modelagem COGS FY26 (calibração refresh), catalisadores.</li><li><strong>2026-05-19</strong>: ingerido <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge\" title=\"raw-md/TSM/2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge\">Morgan Stanley &amp;quot;Agentic AI — The Surge Begins&amp;quot; 11-May-2026</a>. Datapoints Meta-específicos: (1) <strong>Arm &quot;AGI CPU&quot; foi co-desenvolvido COM a Meta</strong> e a demanda já está em <strong>&gt;US$2bn em FYE27-28</strong> (&gt;2x o indicado no Arm Everywhere) — Meta ancorando uma nova classe de CPU de orchestration agentic; (2) <strong>Meta-AWS Graviton</strong>: Meta vai deployar <strong>dezenas de milhões de cores Graviton</strong> para workloads agentic CPU-intensivos, declarando que <strong>&quot;no single chip architecture can serve every workload&quot;</strong> — confirma diversificação multi-vendor descendo para o <strong>CPU layer</strong> (não só accelerator: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MTIA\" title=\"_concepts/MTIA\">MTIA</a>/Broadcom/AMD/NVDA + agora Graviton + Arm AGI CPU). Convergente com <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> (x86-vs-ARM no orchestration) e <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (multi-vendor no CPU). Reforça o pilar &quot;personal superintelligence/agentic&quot; do roadmap Meta pelo lado de infra.</li><li><strong>2026-05-20</strong>: cross-ref <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-earnings-call\">NVDA Q1 FY27 earnings call, 20-May-2026</a> (Colette/Jensen). Datapoints Meta-side: (1) <strong>Meta-MSL listada por Jensen entre os frontier labs construindo em NVDA</strong> (&quot;Anthropic + OpenAI + Gemini + Space xAI + <strong>Meta-MSL</strong> + Microsoft AI + TML + Reflection + Perplexity + Cursor + others&quot;) — primeira menção pública de MSL como cliente frontier NVDA; (2) NVDA confirma <strong>Vera CPU custom Arm cores</strong> com TAM US$200bn — converge com o framing Arm AGI CPU co-desenvolvido com Meta (ver <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a>). Implicação: Meta continua <strong>multi-vendor estrutural</strong> em accelerator (NVDA Grace Hopper SKU + MTIA + Broadcom + AMD + Graviton) E <strong>co-arquiteta</strong> o orchestration CPU agentic (Arm AGI CPU). Cross-link: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MTIA\" title=\"_concepts/MTIA\">MTIA</a> + <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a>.</li></ul></section><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Fontes no vault</h2><h3>Documentos primários (convertidos — Fase 1 + FY25 10-K)</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY22-10-K\">FY22-10-K</a> — FY22 10-K</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY23-10-K\">FY23-10-K</a> — FY23 10-K</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY24-10-K\">FY24-10-K</a> — FY24 10-K</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a> — <strong>FY25 10-K</strong> (baixado via SEC EDGAR 21-Apr-2026, extraído de iXBRL HTML)</li></ul>\n<h3>Documentos internos do Paulo</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2024-01-internal-investment-case\" title=\"raw-md/META/2024-01-internal-investment-case\">2024-01-internal-investment-case</a> — tese original de Long META (Jan/2024)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-02-follow-up\" title=\"raw-md/META/2025-02-follow-up\">2025-02-follow-up</a> — update Feb/2025</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-03-recap\" title=\"raw-md/META/2025-03-recap\">2025-03-recap</a> — <strong>2025 Annual Recap</strong> (framework IWIKs #1-6, muito rico)</li></ul>\n<h3>Research</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-02-ROIC-GEM-Now-LLMs-Later-AustinLyons\" title=\"raw-md/META/2025-02-ROIC-GEM-Now-LLMs-Later-AustinLyons\">2025-02-ROIC-GEM-Now-LLMs-Later-AustinLyons</a> — ✓ OCR&#x27;d 2026-04-23</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-03-Eye-of-the-Hurricane\" title=\"raw-md/META/2025-03-Eye-of-the-Hurricane\">2025-03-Eye-of-the-Hurricane</a> — ✓ OCR&#x27;d 2026-04-23</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-04-FTC-antitrust-case\" title=\"raw-md/META/2025-04-FTC-antitrust-case\">2025-04-FTC-antitrust-case</a> — ✓ OCR&#x27;d 2026-04-23</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-09-Recommender-Model-Evolution-FundaAI\" title=\"raw-md/META/2025-09-Recommender-Model-Evolution-FundaAI\">2025-09-Recommender-Model-Evolution-FundaAI</a> — ✓ OCR&#x27;d 2026-04-23</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-No-Priors-Matt-Steiner-Meta-Ad-System\" title=\"raw-md/META/2026-No-Priors-Matt-Steiner-Meta-Ad-System\">2026-No-Priors-Matt-Steiner-Meta-Ad-System</a> — <em>ingested 2026-04-27</em> — Steiner (VP Monetization Infra) explica stack técnico end-to-end</li></ul>\n<h3>Earnings Calls &amp; Follow-Up Calls — TODOS OCR&#x27;d</h3>\n<p><strong>Earnings Calls oficiais (FY25-FY26):</strong></p>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-Q1-earnings-call\">FY25-Q1-earnings-call</a> — 5 AI opportunities framework; CapEx FY25 raised $60-65B → $64-72B; Llama 4 + Meta AI standalone app launch</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-Q2-earnings-call\">FY25-Q2-earnings-call</a> — <strong>MSL (Meta Superintelligence Labs) criada</strong>; Alexandr Wang CAO + Nat Friedman + Shengjia Zhao; Scale AI $13.8B investment formalizado; first 2026 CapEx step-up signal</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q3-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-Q3-earnings-call\">FY25-Q3-earnings-call</a> — <strong>compute ROI A/B test validated</strong> (&quot;every dollar compute &gt; dollar revenue&quot;); first FY26 CapEx guide $115-135B; $25B bond issuance; OBBBA $18B valuation allowance hit</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-Q4-earnings-call\">FY25-Q4-earnings-call</a> — FY26 CapEx raised to $115-155B (per OCR ⚠️); total expenses guide $162-169B; capacity constrained through 2026; third-party cloud spend explicitly cited</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call</a> — <strong>Q1 FY26 (29-Apr-2026)</strong>: revenue $56.3B beat (+33% YoY); CapEx FY26 raised pra <strong>$125-145B</strong>; contractual commitments <strong>+$107B em Q1</strong>; <strong>Muse Spark released</strong> (1º MSL model); &gt;1GW custom silicon Broadcom; headcount reduction May; price/ad +12%; &gt;$10B ARR creator partnerships; Manus deferred</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY26-Q1-follow-up-call\">FY26-Q1-follow-up-call</a> — <strong>Q1 FY26 follow-up (29-Apr-2026, Susan Li + Chad Heaton)</strong>: macro Iran headwind disclosed (Feb/26 onwards); LPA Q2 &gt; Q1 confirmed; Threads 150M+ DAU; WhatsApp Status hundreds of millions/day mas not meaningful &quot;next few years&quot;; GenAI tools 8M advertisers + 3% conversion gain; cloud strategy explícita (3P bridge 2026-27, 1P DCs future years); CapEx &quot;not optimizing for FCF this year&quot;; Manus &quot;kind of getting undone&quot;; Meta AI Shopping powered by Muse Spark; cross-app integration ainda rudimentary</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Follow-Up Calls (Q&amp;A com analistas pós-earnings) — 13 trimestres FY23/24/25/26-Q1:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>FY23: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-Q1-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY23-Q1-follow-up-call\">FY23-Q1-follow-up-call</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-Q2-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY23-Q2-follow-up-call\">FY23-Q2-follow-up-call</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-Q3-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY23-Q3-follow-up-call\">FY23-Q3-follow-up-call</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-Q4-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY23-Q4-follow-up-call\">FY23-Q4-follow-up-call</a></li><li>FY24: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-Q1-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY24-Q1-follow-up-call\">FY24-Q1-follow-up-call</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-Q2-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY24-Q2-follow-up-call\">FY24-Q2-follow-up-call</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-Q3-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY24-Q3-follow-up-call\">FY24-Q3-follow-up-call</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-Q4-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY24-Q4-follow-up-call\">FY24-Q4-follow-up-call</a></li><li>FY25: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q1-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-Q1-follow-up-call\">FY25-Q1-follow-up-call</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q2-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-Q2-follow-up-call\">FY25-Q2-follow-up-call</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q3-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-Q3-follow-up-call\">FY25-Q3-follow-up-call</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q4-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-Q4-follow-up-call\">FY25-Q4-follow-up-call</a></li><li>FY26: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY26-Q1-follow-up-call\">FY26-Q1-follow-up-call</a> — <em>ingerido 2026-04-30, transcrição PDF→MD direta</em></li></ul>\n<h3>Backlog (em F:\\, não convertidos)</h3>\n<ul><li>10-Ks FY20 e FY21 (Fase 2 se quiser histórico mais longo)</li><li>~37 research reports (MS histórico ignorado per Paulo; BBA, BOFA, Fundamental_Bottom podem entrar em Fase 2)</li><li>xlsx/pptx models (Fase 3)</li></ul>\n<h3>Análises (outputs) — não rodadas</h3>\n<ul><li>[ ] <code>outputs/META/YYYY-MM-DD-pergunta-1-company-analyzer.md</code></li><li>[ ] <code>outputs/META/YYYY-MM-DD-pergunta-2-business-evolution.md</code></li><li>[ ] <code>outputs/META/YYYY-MM-DD-pergunta-3-partner-people.md</code></li><li>[ ] <code>outputs/META/YYYY-MM-DD-pergunta-4-valuation.md</code></li></ul></section></details>", "ic": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Tese de investimento (resumo — framework Paulo IWIKs)</h2><p>Paulo está long META com <strong>IRR esperado de 16% a.a.</strong> (recap Mar/2025). Tese em 6 IWIKs (&quot;What I Want to Know&quot;), estado de evolução em Mar/2025:</p>\n<ol><li><strong>Social network relevância across generations</strong> — EVOLVING POSITIVELY. Family DAP 3.58B (+7% YoY). AI-recommended content &gt;50% do feed (vs ~30% em 2023). Mas Gen Z FB 29%→22% em 5 anos. Moat migrando de <em>social graph</em> pra <em>AI/data flywheel</em> — mais replicável.</li><li><strong>Ad revenue growth com user base maduro</strong> — EVOLVING POSITIVELY. FY25 revenue $201B (+22% YoY). Impressions cresceram pouco; <strong>price/ad +9% YoY</strong> via eficiência AI. Advantage+ $60B+ ARR (3x em ~18m), Reels $50B+ ARR (50x desde mid-2022).</li><li><strong>AI impact em engagement + monetização</strong> — EVOLVING POSITIVELY. GEM (+3.5% ad clicks — <strong>citado pelo Jensen na <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVDA\" title=\"wiki/NVDA\">NVDA</a> Q4 FY26 call</strong>), Lattice (+3-4%), Sequence Learning (+1%+). Mas Meta AI tem 1B MAU e <strong>zero receita standalone</strong>.</li><li><strong>TikTok &amp; competitive dynamics</strong> — LARGELY RESOLVED. JV US (Oracle/Silver Lake/MGX) finalizado em 24-Jan-2026. Durante outage Jan/2025: Meta CPMs +10-12%, ad spend +22.4%. YT Shorts é o competidor estrutural mais sério.</li><li><strong>CapEx monetization &amp; capital returns</strong> — <strong>OPEN -- CRITICAL</strong>. FY25 CapEx <strong>$72.22B</strong> (+85% YoY — <strong>oficialmente confirmado no 10-K FY25</strong>). <strong>Contractual commitments explodiram de $32.8B (Dec/24) pra $131.05B (Dec/25) — +$98B em um ano (4x)</strong>, &quot;mostly related to third-party cloud capacity arrangements&quot;. <strong>Q1 FY26 update: +$107B em UM trimestre</strong> (Mar/2026 implícito ~$238B), driven by &quot;multiyear cloud deals + infrastructure purchase agreements&quot; (cloud capacity coming online 2026-2027). Ver seção &quot;Third-party cloud spending&quot; abaixo. <strong>FY26 guide raised pra $125-145B</strong> (na Q1 FY26 call), driver: &quot;higher component pricing, particularly memory pricing&quot;. FCF caiu pra $43.6B (-16% YoY). LG Model projeta <strong>FCF negativo em FY26 (-$8.7B)</strong> antes de recuperar. <strong>Susan reconheceu publicamente: &quot;we have continued to underestimate our compute needs&quot;</strong> — sinal implícito de novo step-up em 2027. É a pergunta-chave da tese.</li><li><strong>Regulatory impact</strong> — STRUCTURAL RISK — MONITORING. EU: DMA fine €200M, DSA potential €12B+, GDPR cumulativo €2.5B. <strong>LPA (Less Personalized Ads)</strong>: Dec/25 alignment com EC sobre changes ao consent model na Europa; <strong>Q1 FY26 europeus começaram a ver mudanças</strong>; <strong>Susan confirmou Q2 impact &gt; Q1</strong> (&quot;rolling out updated offering through Q1 → Q2 e beyond têm full quarter impact&quot;) — factored em Q2 guide. Susan Q1 FY26 follow-up: &quot;changes go far above and beyond what&#x27;s required by the DMA itself, and <strong>our appeal of the commission&#x27;s decision will continue in the courts</strong>&quot; — sinalização defensiva forte. Youth safety: 42+ state AGs, 1,700+ MDL cases; LA court ruling levantou preocupação back-half mas mgmt &quot;premature to comment&quot; + &quot;we will defend our record vigorously&quot;. IRS dispute: $54B alegado / $16B potencial.</li></ol>\n<p><strong>Grande mudança 2025</strong>: Meta deixou de ser &quot;efficiency company&quot; (2023-2024 &quot;Year of Efficiency&quot;) e reassumiu como <strong>&quot;AI infrastructure company&quot;</strong> — Q2/25 criou Superintelligence Labs, Q4/25 virou 2026 &quot;Year of AI Acceleration&quot;, criou Meta Strategic Infrastructure (MSI) e Meta Compute, fez <strong>deal $100B+ com AMD (6GW)</strong> e <strong>6.6GW nuclear via Vistra</strong>, emitiu $30B em bonds num único trimestre. <strong>Também oficialmente</strong>: (i) Scale AI minority investment de <strong>$13.80B</strong> closed em 2025 (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a> Note 5), (ii) JV Louisiana data center <strong>co-development</strong> (Oct/2025) — &quot;strategic optionality&quot; per 10-K, (iii) long-term debt subiu de ~$37B pra <strong>$58.74B</strong> em FY25 (funding CapEx).</p>\n<p><strong>Q1 FY26 milestones (29-Apr-2026 call)</strong>: (i) <strong>Muse Spark released</strong> — primeiro modelo de Meta Superintelligence Labs (10 meses do stand-up à release, &quot;fastest from standing up the lab to having a widely accepted strong model&quot;); (ii) <strong>Meta Compute initiative</strong> + rolando <strong>&gt;1GW de custom silicon (Broadcom)</strong> + AMD chips + new Nvidia systems — diversificação multi-vendor; (iii) <strong>headcount reduction em May 2026</strong> anunciado (&quot;leaner operating model&quot;); (iv) <strong>revenue beat</strong> $56.3B (+33% YoY) above guide; (v) <strong>price/ad +12% YoY</strong> (vs +5% Q4) — eficiência AI compoundando; (vi) <strong>2027 CapEx step-up sinalizado</strong> (Susan: &quot;we have continued to underestimate our compute needs&quot;). Ver <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Q1 FY26 follow-up call (29-Apr-2026, Susan + Chad Heaton)</strong> — <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-follow-up-call\" title=\"raw-md/META/FY26-Q1-follow-up-call\">FY26-Q1-follow-up-call</a> — adições materiais: (a) <strong>macro headwind Iran</strong>: Susan revelou &quot;reduction in advertiser spend coinciding with the beginning of the conflict in Iran at the end of February, continued through the quarter&quot;, most pronounced em Middle East user region mas com <strong>softer trends também em US e Western Europe</strong> — primeiro reconhecimento explícito de macro hit na história recente; signs of improvement em April; Q2 guide embeds range &quot;from continued improvement to macro deceleration&quot;; (b) <strong>LPA Q2 maior que Q1</strong>: Susan confirmou que &quot;revenue impact from updated user flows will be larger in Q2 than it was in Q1&quot; (rollout em curso durante Q1; full quarter impact em Q2+); appeal continua; impact factored em Q2 outlook; (c) <strong>Threads 150M+ DAU</strong>, ads em 200+ países, &quot;not meaningful driver of impression or revenue growth this year&quot;; (d) <strong>WhatsApp Status ads = hundreds of millions of viewers/dia</strong>, global rollout this year, mas estrutural: <strong>&quot;not meaningful contributor to total impressions or revenue growth for the next few years&quot;</strong> — geo mix LatAm/Asia/Africa = lower ad spend per capita, ad targeting menos robusto pra users sem Meta Account Center linking; (e) <strong>GenAI ad-creative tools: 8M+ advertisers</strong> (vs 4M end of 2024 — 2x em ~16 meses), vasta maioria SMBs; <strong>+3% conversion gain em video generation</strong> test; (f) <strong>Manus M&amp;A &quot;kind of getting undone&quot;</strong> (analyst Nick Jones framing) — Susan deferred mas confirmou &quot;lot of confidence em agentic roadmap&quot;; (g) <strong>CapEx posture</strong>: &quot;we aren&#x27;t really optimizing for a specific cash flow level this year&quot;; (h) <strong>OpEx puts/takes</strong>: workforce reduction savings offset by restructuring costs intra-FY26 → expense outlook unchanged; (i) <strong>Cloud strategy explícita</strong>: third-party multi-year cloud contracts trazem capacity online &quot;more quickly this year and next year&quot;; owned/leased DC = &quot;for capacity that comes online in future years&quot;; (j) <strong>Meta AI cross-app integration ainda rudimentary</strong> — Gmail mentioned como example; &quot;vast majority of journey ahead&quot;; 3 diferenciadores citados: social graph + first-party signals, messaging como agent surface, Ray-Ban Meta Glasses como form factor.</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Vantagem competitiva (moat)</h2><p><em>Análise profunda na Pergunta 1.</em> Hipóteses atuais:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Escala de usuários (3.58B DAP)</strong>: moat histórico = <em>social graph</em>. Dificílimo de replicar.</li><li><strong>Moat em transição</strong>: conforme AI-recommended content passa de 30% pra &gt;50% do feed, Meta depende menos de &quot;friends connection&quot; e mais de <em>data/compute flywheel</em> pra qualidade de recomendação. Isso muda o tipo de moat — mais replicável em princípio, mas Meta tem data set proprietário de 3.58B users que concorrentes não têm.</li><li><strong>AI ad targeting</strong>: eficiência compounding. Price/ad +9% YoY sustentado em user base maduro. Meta está <strong>deflationary pro advertiser</strong> (better ROAS) e <strong>inflationary pro Meta</strong> (higher revenue per conversion).</li><li><strong>Distribution advantage</strong>: IG Reels ganhou da TikTok no uso interno; WhatsApp tem 2B+ users globais.</li><li><strong>MTIA (Meta&#x27;s custom ASIC)</strong>: em FY25 estendeu do training pra ranking workloads. Em tese reduz dependência de <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVDA\" title=\"wiki/NVDA\">NVDA</a> e cria cost advantage estrutural. Ver <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a>.</li><li><strong>Content ecosystem</strong>: creator economy, GenAI creative tools baixam custo de produção de criativos.</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Riscos</h2><h3>Declarados pelo management</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>LPA (Less Personalized Ads) EU</strong>: CFO reconheceu impacto direto em receita (2025). Europa = ~16% da receita. Se framework se espalhar pra India/Brasil/Austrália, impacto sobe.</li><li><strong>Youth safety litigation</strong>: 10-K FY24 descreve como podendo resultar em &quot;material loss&quot;.</li><li><strong>IRS dispute</strong>: $54B alleged / $16B potential one-time.</li></ul>\n<h3>Estruturais</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>CapEx sem monetização comprovada</strong>: $125-145B em FY26 sem linkage claro a revenue novo. &quot;Strategic necessity&quot; vs &quot;proven ROI&quot; (IWIK #5). <strong>Susan Q1 FY26 follow-up</strong>: &quot;we aren&#x27;t really optimizing for a specific cash flow level this year&quot; — confirmação explícita de que FCF não é guardrail.</li><li><strong>Moat em transição</strong>: de social graph (irreplicável) pra AI compute/data (capital-intensive, potencialmente replicável).</li><li><strong>Ad model regulatório</strong>: LPA tipo framework ameaça o AI targeting que é a fonte de todo o growth. <strong>Q1 FY26 follow-up: Susan confirmou Q2 LPA impact &gt; Q1</strong>.</li><li><strong>Reality Labs</strong>: perpetual losses. Se gla sses não pegarem ritmo maior, é drain permanente.</li><li><strong>Controlling shareholder</strong>: Zuckerberg pode decidir bets grandes sem input de minoritários. Histórico tem wins e misses.</li><li><strong>🆕 Macro sensitivity</strong>: Q1 FY26 follow-up revelou que conflito Iran (Feb/26) gerou redução em advertiser spend não só Middle East mas também <strong>US e Western Europe</strong>. Sinal de que ad revenue Meta tem beta real a eventos geopolíticos — não é &quot;macro-proof&quot; como narrativa anterior sugeria.</li></ul>\n<h3>Competitivos</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>YouTube Shorts</strong>: 200B daily views, 5.91% engagement. Google tem data + compute. Mais sério estrutural que TikTok JV.</li><li><strong>AI attention competitors</strong>: ChatGPT, Gemini capturam atenção que antes ia pra Meta AI.</li><li><strong>Apple privacy framework</strong>: continua restringindo first-party data advantage vs competidores (ATT impact $10B em 2022).</li></ul></section>", "val": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Valuation (snapshot)</h2><p><em>Análise profunda na Pergunta 4.</em> Pontos-chave (Mar/2025 recap):</p>\n<ul><li><strong>P/E NTM: ~21x</strong> (vs avg 5Y de ~20x). Não &quot;cheap&quot; historicamente mas razoável dado growth.</li><li><strong>Esperado IRR 16% p.a.</strong> (Paulo&#x27;s base case 3Y). EPS growth 12-15% p.a. + small rerating.</li><li><strong>LG Model projeta revenue $519B em 2032</strong> (12.9% CAGR FY25-FY32). Operating margins: 41.4% → 36% (2026 trough) → 38% (2032).</li><li><strong>Asymmetric setup FY26</strong>: se mgmt estiver certo sobre AI returns, trough de FCF é entry opportunity. Se errado, é início de ciclo de capital destruction.</li><li><strong>Optionality não considerada no base case</strong>: Meta AI monetization standalone, Reality Labs turnaround, new initiatives.</li></ul></section>", "pa": "<div class=\"empty-view\"><p>Sem dados de <strong>Historical Price Action</strong> na wiki ainda.</p><p class=\"hint\">Esta view será populada quando a seção correspondente existir em <code>wiki/META.md</code>.</p></div>", "er": "<div class=\"empty-view\"><p>Sem dados de <strong>Earnings Review</strong> na wiki ainda.</p><p class=\"hint\">Esta view será populada quando a seção correspondente existir em <code>wiki/META.md</code>.</p></div>", "insider": "<div class=\"empty-view\"><p>Sem dados de <strong>Insider Trading</strong> na wiki ainda.</p><p class=\"hint\">Esta view será populada quando a seção correspondente existir em <code>wiki/META.md</code>.</p></div>"}, "source": "wiki/META.md", "built_at": "2026-06-09"};
